parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and failure of brake lines can cause the brake pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop or slow down
brake fluid leaks
and the service brake system light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause the speedometer, oil pressure gauge, and other gauges to malfunction or not work at all, leading to a driving hazard and potential accidents.
symptoms: The speedometer displays incorrect or erratic readings
the oil pressure gauge drops to 0
and other gauges may not function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to a safety hazard and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or does not start
the battery drains
and the anti-theft system may cause the engine to quit while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the anti-theft system can cause the engine to quit while driving, leading to a safety hazard and potential accidents.
symptoms: The engine quits while driving
and the vehicle may not restart.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the HVAC blower motor can cause the blower to not function properly, leading to discomfort and potential health issues.
symptoms: The blower motor does not function properly
and the blower speed settings may not work correctly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A cracked dashboard can lead to airbag deployment issues, which can cause injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Cracking or breaking of the dashboard near the airbag and windshield area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake system failure can cause extended stopping distances, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal travels almost to the floor
extended stopping distances
rusted brake lines
and master cylinder issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rust corrosion can cause structural failures, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Rusted brake and fuel lines
rusted spare tire carrier
and rusted structural components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rear window hinge failure can cause the window to separate from the vehicle, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Rear window hinge breaks
loud popping noise
sudden increase in wind noise
and structural failure of the rear tailgate window hatch.
